Sanitizer

Interface SQLRules


  • public interface SQLRules
    Defines list of Rules that any SQL statement must satisfy before reaching to database. List of rules defined here provides a protection from SQL-Injection by checking any irregular expressions and stop words. Some methods in this interface assumes classes implementing this interface must contain variables listed below

    • String TOKEN_ORACLE_HINT_START

      Starting of comment syntax for orace database query

    • String TOKEN_ORACLE_HINT_END

      Ending of comment syntax for orace database query

    • String[] ILLEGAL_CHARACTERS

      List of character that are not supposed to be in a standard SQL statement

    • String[] STOP_WORDS

      List of words that are not supposed to be in a standard SQL CRUD statement

    • String[] STOP_WORDS_MONGO

      List of words that are not supposed to be in a standard Mongo CRUD statement

    Since:
    1.8
    Author:
    Saurab Dahal
